arts.ttl: Stevenage claim first League One away win at Mansfield Town
arts.sum: Mansfield did have other chances, a low free-kick was pushed round the post by Cooper after a deflection, and they were urged on by a crowd who were equal parts encouraging and furious at the referee. Mansfield's start to the season meant Boro found a home side full of confidence and it was no surprise that the opening exchanges, for perhaps 15 minutes, belonged to the Stags.

arts.ttl: Jake Young’s goal gives Stevenage victory and ends Mansfield’s winning home run
arts.sum: The visitors were victorious in Nottinghamshire.

arts.ttl: Stevenage at Mansfield Town in League One - Alex Revell preview
arts.sum: "The result in the league against Peterborough, just the way it happened and how well we played in that game, to come away with nothing, psychologically that takes a lot out of you. He's got them playing some really good football at the moment and the results of speaking for themselves.

arts.ttl: Stevenage injury update ahead of Mansfield Town trip
